@schema_version 1
@project naudit_query_mode_test
@description Test fixture for WP-009 Phase 2 query-mode rules. The rule below ships NO bnf_fragment block; the engine must locate the named violation_nt in the base C grammar (c_ncc.bnf) directly and report one violation per match.
@source_doc test/fixtures/naudit/guidance_query_mode.bnf
@dependencies

@rule naudit.test.query_mode
@language c
@title query-mode function_definition match (test only)
@section test
@violation_nt function_definition
@rationale Phase 2 test rule: every <function_definition> match in the audited source file should become a violation. No bnf_fragment is provided; the engine should find the NT in c_ncc.bnf directly.
@bad (any function definition)
@good (none)
@guidance Query-mode rule with no BNF fragment.
